player.seasonOutlook: Bridges will look to pick up where he left off two seasons ago as a top-20 player in fantasy when he averaged 20.1 PPG, 7.0 RPG and 3.8 APG. After being arrested on domestic violence charges last summer, he never signed with a team. Bridges now returns after signing a one-year deal with the Hornets this summer. Bridges has been off the court for quite some time and there is some uncertainty when drafting him, which is causing him to slide in fantasy drafts.

Mathurin averaged 16.7 PPG, 4.1 RPG and 1.5 APG in 28.5 MPG as a rookie last season, and was one of three players around the league to score at least 1,000 points off the bench. In the offseason, the Pacers signed Bruce Brown to a two-year deal, traded for Obi Toppin and drafted Jarace Walker. The amount of minutes Mathurin plays should remain the same despite the additions. He has top-100 upside if he can improve his 3-point shooting. Mathurin's scoring ability makes him a better option in points leagues than category leagues.
